Description: Corroded iron chisel, of circular cross-section, with a slightly flattened cutting edge on one side, and a tapering flat-tipped tang on the other.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19
Curator's comments: One of the "chisels (pl. xxxviii. 15 to 20), of which about forty were kept, beside many rejected", mentioned by Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 78 § 78, p. 110, pl. xxxviii, 18.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 78 § 78, p. 110, pl. xxxviii, 18)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.46, p.75, p.184, pl.26)
